quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,60,"It is He who takes your souls by night, and He knows what you do by day, then He reanimates you therein so that a specified term may be completed. Then to Him will be your return, whereat He will inform you concerning what you used to do"
  6,61,"He is the All-dominant over His servants, and He sends guards to [protect] you. When death approaches anyone of you, Our messengers take him away and they do not neglect [their duty]"
  6,62,"Then they are returned to Allah, their real master. Look! All judgement belongs to Him, and He is the swiftest of reckoners"
  6,63,"Say, ‘Who delivers you from the darkness of land and sea, [when] You invoke Him suppliantly and secretly: ‘‘If He delivers us from this, we will surely be among the grateful’’?’"
  6,64,"Say, ‘It is Allah who delivers you from them and from every agony, [but] then you ascribe partners [to Him].’"
  6,65,"Say, ‘He is able to send upon you a punishment from above you or from under your feet, or confound you as [hostile] factions, and make you taste one another’s violence.’ Look, how We paraphrase the signs variously so that they may understand"
  6,66,"Your people have denied it, though it is the truth. Say, ‘It is not my business to watch over you.’"
  6,67,"For every prophecy there is a [preordained] setting, and soon you will know"
  6,68,"When you see those who gossip impiously about Our signs, avoid them until they engage in some other discourse; but if Satan makes you forget, then, after remembering, do not sit with the wrongdoing lot"